LLMs capture contextual probabilities of tokens in the parameters of a large neural network, often following the Transformer architecture [DBLP:conf/nips/VaswaniSPUJGKP17].
 The model parameters are computed by two stages of training: {\em unsupervised pre-training} and {\em supervised fine-tuning}.
 LLMs can also benefit from inference-time (i.e., post-training) techniques, most notably, {\em prompt engineering} [DBLP:journals/csur/LiuYFJHN23] and {\em in-context learning} [DBLP:journals/corr/abs-2301-00234].